# FlyRank Frontend Capstone Rules

## Project Context

This repository is for the FlyRank AI Internship Frontend track capstone project.

Current assignment:

- FE-01: Environment and AI Toolchain
- Phase: Setup

## Stack

- Cursor as the AI-assisted IDE
- Git and GitHub for version control
- Node.js and npm for frontend tooling
- HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and TypeScript as needed

## Working Style

- Keep changes simple and easy to understand.
- Explain the purpose of changes before applying them.
- Do not create or modify many files at once unless requested.
- Prefer beginner-friendly explanations.
- Keep documentation updated as the project evolves.

## Git Convention

Use Conventional Commits:

- docs: documentation changes
- chore: setup, tooling, configuration
- feat: new features
- fix: bug fixes
- refactor: internal code improvements

Example:

docs: update README setup notes
